                <li><strong>Attribution:</strong> When your User Content is published, we will provide attribution to you as the author, using your profile name or username.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>2. Content Standards and Requirements:</h3>

            <ol>
                <li><strong>Original Work:</strong> You represent and warrant that all User Content you submit is your original work or that you have obtained all necessary rights and permissions to submit it.</li>
                <li><strong>Educational Value:</strong> User Content must have educational value and be relevant to learning SQL and database concepts.</li>
                <li><strong>Quality Standards:</strong> Tasks should be clear, well-structured, and include:
                    <ul>
                        <li>A descriptive title</li>
                        <li>Clear task description</li>
                        <li>Appropriate hints (where applicable)</li>
                        <li>Valid SQL solutions</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Accuracy:</strong> You are responsible for ensuring the technical accuracy of your User Content, including SQL queries and expected results.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>3. Prohibited Content:</h3>

            <p>You agree not to submit User Content that:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Violates any applicable laws or regulations</li>
                <li>Infringes upon the intellectual property rights of others</li>
                <li>Contains malicious code, SQL injection attempts, or harmful instructions</li>
                <li>Includes offensive, defamatory, discriminatory, or inappropriate language</li>
                <li>Contains spam, advertising, or promotional material unrelated to SQL education</li>
                <li>Violates the privacy rights of any individual</li>
                <li>Is duplicate or substantially similar to existing content on SQLtest</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>4. Review and Moderation:</h3>

